<h1>Questionable Features</h1>
<h2>in Tribes: Ascend - 08/04/12</h2>

<h4>Suiciding</h4>
<br>Tribes: Ascend has a hotkey to suicide, and suiciding is extremely useful in Tribes, which is kind of an unusual thing to say.  Here are some useful reasons to suicide:
<ul>
<li>Changing class.</li>
<li>Refilling ammo.</li>
<li>Returning to the base to defend after getting out of position.</li>
<li>A combination of switching to a light class and getting into a better position to chase a flag carrier.</li>
</ul>
The problem with suiciding is that it is not really intuitive as being a beneficial thing to do and becoming better at the game.
<br><br>
<h4>Boosting</h4>
<br>A common thing to do in Tribes is to boost yourself by hitting yourself with any explosive weapon to gain speed.  This is useful for grabbing the flag and for chasing flag carriers.  The problem is that it's not really intuitive to hurt yourself to benefit you.  I was thinking about this, but then I saw the patch preview video for the most recent patch, where they increased the knockback on explosive weapons by 20% to make this feature even more important.  So I guess they don't see any problem with it being intuitive, and are encouraging players to do it.
